---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const faq = [
  {
    question: "What is the difference between JSONCraft and JSON Crack?",
    answer: "JSON Crack is a visual JSON editor that displays JSON as an interactive graph or tree diagram. JSONCraft is a suite of 23 developer tools that includes JSON formatting, diffing, conversion to YAML/CSV/TOML, regex testing, and more. JSON Crack excels at visualizing complex JSON structures; JSONCraft excels at transforming and validating data.",
  },
  {
    question: "Does JSONCraft have a graph view like JSON Crack?",
    answer: "No. JSONCraft includes a collapsible tree viewer for exploring JSON, but not a visual graph. JSON Crack's interactive graph view is its unique feature — it displays nodes, edges, and relationships in a way that makes nested JSON structures easier to understand visually.",
  },
  {
    question: "Is JSON Crack free?",
    answer: "JSON Crack has a free tier for basic use. The Premium plan ($6/month) unlocks larger file support, comparison features, and additional export options. JSONCraft is entirely free with no paid tier.",
  },
  {
    question: "Can JSONCraft convert JSON to other formats like JSON Crack?",
    answer: "JSONCraft has more conversion options. It supports bidirectional conversion between JSON and YAML, CSV, TOML, and TypeScript, plus JSON to HTML table. JSON Crack focuses on visualization and does not offer the same breadth of format conversions.",
  },
];

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  mainEntity: faq.map((item) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    name: item.question,
    acceptedAnswer: { "@type": "Answer", text: item.answer },
  })),
};

const articleJsonLd = JSON.stringify({
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: "JSONCraft vs JSON Crack: JSON Visualization Tools Compared",
  description: "JSONCraft and JSON Crack both visualize JSON as interactive graphs. Compare visualization features, privacy, and extra tools like format conversion.",
  image: "https://jsoncraft.dev/og-image.png",
  author: { "@type": "Organization", name: "JSONCraft", url: "https://jsoncraft.dev" },
  publisher: {
    "@type": "Organization",
    name: "JSONCraft",
    logo: { "@type": "ImageObject", url: "https://jsoncraft.dev/og-image.png" },
  },
  datePublished: "2026-04-09",
  dateModified: "2026-04-10",
  mainEntityOfPage: "https://jsoncraft.dev/vs-json-crack/",
  inLanguage: "en",
});
---

<Layout
  title="JSONCraft vs JSON Crack"
  description="Detailed comparison between JSONCraft and JSON Crack. Visualization, tool breadth, pricing, and use cases compared."
  activeToolId="compare"
  lang="en"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={articleJsonLd} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />
  <div class="flex-1 overflow-auto px-6 py-8">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8 text-sm" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">
      <div>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: var(--color-accent);">Comparison</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2">JSONCraft vs JSON Crack</h2>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">An honest comparison between a developer toolkit and a visual JSON editor. Last updated: 2026-04-09.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Overview -->
      <section class="space-y-3" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Overview</h3>
        <p>
          <strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">JSONCraft</strong> is a free collection of 23 developer tools for JSON formatting, diffing, conversion (YAML, CSV, TOML, TypeScript), and common utilities like regex, hash, UUID, and base64. All tools run client-side in the browser.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">JSON Crack</strong> (jsoncrack.com) is a visual JSON editor that renders JSON as interactive graph diagrams. With over 30,000 GitHub stars, it is one of the most popular JSON visualization tools. Free tier available; Premium at $6/month.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Comparison table -->
      <section>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Feature Comparison</h3>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="w-full text-sm border border-[var(--color-border)] rounded">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-[var(--color-bg-tertiary)]">
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Feature</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSONCraft</th>
                <th class="text-left px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSON Crack</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Primary focus</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Multi-tool suite (23 tools)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Visual JSON editor</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Graph visualization</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (interactive nodes/edges)</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Tree viewer</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (collapsible)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (graph-based)</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSON formatting</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (CodeMirror 6)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSON diff</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (side-by-side)</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Premium only</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSONPath tester</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">JSON Schema validation</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Format conversions</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">YAML, CSV, TOML, TypeScript, HTML table</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Limited</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Dev utilities</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Regex, hash, UUID, base64, cron, timestamps</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Export as image</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes (PNG, SVG)</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Open source</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">No</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Yes</td></tr>
              <tr><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Price</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Free</td><td class="px-4 py-2 border-b border-[var(--color-border)]">Free + $6/month Premium</td></tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Where JSONCraft wins -->
      <section class="space-y-3" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Where JSONCraft wins</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Tool breadth.</strong> 23 tools: JSON diff, YAML/CSV/TOML converters, regex tester, hash generator, UUID generator, cron builder, and more. JSON Crack focuses primarily on visualization.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Format conversion.</strong> Bidirectional converters for YAML, CSV, TOML, and TypeScript interfaces. JSON Crack does not offer the same conversion coverage.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">JSON Schema validation.</strong> Validate data against any JSON Schema draft with detailed error paths. Not available in JSON Crack.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Completely free.</strong> Every feature is available at no cost. JSON Crack locks diff and some export features behind Premium.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">JSONPath tester.</strong> Write and evaluate JSONPath expressions in real time against your data.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Where JSON Crack wins -->
      <section class="space-y-3" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Where JSON Crack wins</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Visual graph view.</strong> JSON Crack's signature feature: see your JSON as an interactive graph with nodes and edges. This makes deeply nested structures far easier to understand than plain text or a tree view.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Image export.</strong> Export your JSON visualization as PNG or SVG for documentation, presentations, or sharing with teammates.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Open source.</strong> JSON Crack is open source with 30,000+ GitHub stars and an active community contributing improvements.</li>
          <li><strong style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Understanding complex structures.</strong> When you need to make sense of a deeply nested API response or configuration file, a visual graph is more intuitive than scrolling through text.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Verdict -->
      <section class="space-y-3" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Verdict</h3>
        <p>
          These tools solve different problems. JSON Crack is the best choice when you need to understand the shape of complex JSON visually or export diagrams. JSONCraft is the better choice when you need to transform data (convert to YAML, CSV, or TOML), validate against schemas, diff two documents, or access common dev utilities — all for free and fully client-side.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="space-y-4" style="color: var(--color-text-secondary);">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
        {faq.map((item) => (
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-medium mb-1" style="color: var(--color-text-primary);">{item.question}</h4>
            <p>{item.answer}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
